sentences.english: They appeared full, but no, there was one empty cubicle.
sentences.chinese: 看上去已经满员的厕所里还有一个空档位。

sentences.english: Once the event queues fill up, new event messages for that queue are discarded.
sentences.chinese: 一旦事件队列满员，那个队列的新消息将被丢弃。

sentences.english: It is equally inconvenient if that subscription queue fills up.
sentences.chinese: 同样，如果订阅队列满员，就会很不方便。

sentences.english: Cairns and Townsville fly flights are full.
sentences.chinese: 飞离凯恩斯和汤斯维尔的航班皆满员。

sentences.english: Now, most universities and middle schools have stopped hiring for the fall semester.
sentences.chinese: 现在大多数大学和中学的秋季学期招聘都满员儿了。

sentences.english: He also said that many prisons are filled to three or four times their capacity.
sentences.chinese: 他还说，许多监狱囚犯人数是满员的三到四倍。

sentences.english: After the boarding process, I settled into my seat in the Business Class cabin, which was full.
sentences.chinese: 登机以后，我在公务舱落座，舱内已经满员了。

sentences.english: It's just crazy, like our classes are getting really full.
sentences.chinese: 这很疯狂，像我们班都已经满员了。

definition: to expand (esp. by new recruitment)/to increase the army/to augment
to dress (troops)/to line up (to arrange in a straight line)
on call/always available/ready at all times
to stay behind to take care of things
to change shift/the next work shift/to relieve (a workman on the previous shift)/to take over the job
quota/number of places/place (in an institution, a group etc)
